.\" Manpage for anvil.
.\" Contact: https://github.com/siddhantbhattarai/anvil
.TH ANVIL 1 "2026-06-16" "anvil 0.6.0" "ANVIL Security Scanner Manual"
.SH NAME
anvil \- adversarial web application vulnerability scanner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B anvil
.B \-t
.I URL
.RB [ \-p
.IR PARAM ]
.RI [ CLASS-FLAGS ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.br
.B anvil
.B \-\-target
.I URL
.B \-\-all
.RB [ \-\-crawl ]
.RB [ \-o
.IR FILE ]
.RB [ \-\-format
.IR FORMAT ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ANVIL
is an enterprise-grade, evidence-driven web application security scanner.
It detects and safely proves five classes of vulnerability with a low
false-positive rate, then emits machine-readable reports suitable for triage
and continuous-integration gating.
.PP
Each finding is confirmed by observable evidence (a database error or boolean
oracle, JavaScript execution, an out-of-band callback, command output, or a
file-content signature) rather than by payload reflection alone, so reflected
input cannot by itself raise a finding.
.PP
Run a single targeted check by combining
.B \-t/\-\-target
and
.B \-p/\-\-param
with one class flag (for example
.BR \-\-sqli ),
or sweep every class with
.BR \-\-all .
When a parameter is not given explicitly, ANVIL discovers testable parameters
from the target URL and, with
.BR \-\-crawl ,
from the wider application.
.SH DETECTION CLASSES
.TP
.B \-\-sqli
SQL injection (CWE-89). Boolean, error, union, time-based, stacked,
out-of-band, and second-order techniques. See
.B SQLI DETECTION
options.
.TP
.B \-\-xss
Cross-site scripting (CWE-79). Reflected by default; stored, DOM, and blind
modes via
.B XSS DETECTION
options.
.TP
.B \-\-ssrf
Server-side request forgery (CWE-918). Internal ranges, cloud metadata
endpoints, and non-HTTP schemes via
.B SSRF DETECTION
options.
.TP
.B \-\-cmdi
OS command injection (CWE-78). Output-based and time-based detection.
.TP
.BR \-\-path\-traversal ", " \-\-lfi
Path traversal / local file inclusion (CWE-22). Confirmed only when a known
file's content signature appears in the response.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Core features
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-target \fIURL\fR
Target URL. Required. Example:
.IR https://example.com/page.php?id=1 .
.TP
.B \-\-all
Enable all vulnerability scans.
.TP
.B \-\-fingerprint
Fingerprint server, operating system, and framework.
.TP
.B \-\-crawl
Crawl the application and discover parameters.
.TP
.B \-\-js\-crawl
Render JavaScript with headless Chrome while crawling to find SPA routes,
forms, and XHR/fetch APIs a static crawl misses.
.TP
.BR \-\-sqli ", " \-\-xss ", " \-\-ssrf ", " \-\-cmdi ", " \-\-path\-traversal
Enable an individual detection class (see
.BR "DETECTION CLASSES" ).
.SS XSS detection
.TP
.B \-\-xss\-all
Enable all XSS types (reflected, stored, DOM, blind).
.TP
.B \-\-xss\-stored
Stored / persistent XSS.
.TP
.B \-\-xss\-dom
DOM-based XSS (client-side analysis).
.TP
.B \-\-xss\-blind
Blind XSS using out-of-band callbacks.
.TP
.B \-\-callback \fIDOMAIN\fR
Callback domain for blind XSS. Requires
.BR \-\-xss\-blind .
.TP
.B \-\-max\-payloads \fIN\fR
Maximum payloads per context (default: 20).
.TP
.B \-\-xss\-context \fICONTEXT\fR
Target context: html, attribute, js_string, js_code, url, polyglot.
.SS SSRF detection
.TP
.B \-\-ssrf\-all
Enable all SSRF types (internal, metadata, schemes).
.TP
.B \-\-ssrf\-internal
Test internal ranges (RFC1918, loopback, link-local).
.TP
.B \-\-ssrf\-metadata
Test cloud metadata endpoints (AWS, GCP, Azure).
.TP
.B \-\-ssrf\-schemes
Test non-HTTP schemes (file, gopher, ftp, dict).
.TP
.B \-\-ssrf\-callback \fIDOMAIN\fR
Callback domain for blind SSRF.
.TP
.B \-\-ssrf\-max\-payloads \fIN\fR
Maximum payloads per parameter (default: 20).
.SS SQL injection detection
.TP
.B \-\-sqli\-all
Enable all SQLi techniques.
.TP
.B \-\-time\-sqli
Time-based (blind) SQLi.
.TP
.B \-\-stacked
Stacked-query SQLi.
.TP
.B \-\-oob
Out-of-band SQLi.
.TP
.B \-\-oob\-callback \fIDOMAIN\fR
Callback domain for OOB detection.
.TP
.B \-\-second\-order
Second-order SQLi.
.TP
.B \-\-technique \fIBEUTS\fR
Techniques to use: B=Boolean, E=Error, U=Union, T=Time, S=Stacked
(default: BEUTS).
.SS Enumeration (post-exploitation, authorized use only)
.TP
.BR \-\-dbs ", " \-\-tables ", " \-\-columns ", " \-\-schema
Enumerate databases, tables, columns, or the full schema.
.TP
.BR \-\-count ", " \-\-dump ", " \-\-dump\-all
Count rows; dump a table; dump all tables. See
.B RULES OF ENGAGEMENT.
.TP
.B \-D, \-\-database \fINAME\fR ; \-T, \-\-table \fINAME\fR ; \-C, \-\-col \fILIST\fR
Scope enumeration to a database, table, or column list.
.TP
.B \-\-start \fIN\fR ; \-\-stop \fIN\fR
First and last row to retrieve.
.SS Database / user info
.TP
.BR \-\-banner ", " \-\-current\-user ", " \-\-current\-db ", " \-\-hostname ", " \-\-is\-dba
Retrieve DBMS banner, current user, current database, hostname, or DBA status.
.TP
.BR \-\-users ", " \-\-passwords ", " \-\-privileges ", " \-\-roles
Enumerate DBMS users, password hashes, privileges, or roles.
.TP
.BR \-\-crack " " \-\-wordlist \fIFILE\fR
Crack retrieved hashes with a dictionary (built-in list if no wordlist given).
.SS Authentication
.TP
.B \-\-cookie \fISTRING\fR
Cookie string for authenticated scanning.
.TP
.B \-H, \-\-header \fIHEADER\fR
Extra HTTP header; repeatable.
.SS Injection point
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-param \fINAME\fR
Parameter to test directly (skips discovery).
.TP
.B \-\-data \fIDATA\fR
POST body to test.
.TP
.B \-\-method \fIMETHOD\fR
HTTP method, GET or POST (default: GET).
.TP
.B \-\-trigger\-url \fIURL\fR
Trigger URL for second-order SQLi.
.TP
.BR \-\-extra\-data ", " \-\-prefix ", " \-\-suffix
Extra POST data, and a prefix/suffix wrapped around each payload.
.SS Tuning
.TP
.B \-\-threshold \fIFLOAT\fR
Detection confidence threshold, 0.0\(en1.0 (default: 0.5).
.TP
.B \-\-risk \fIN\fR
Risk level: 1=safe, 2=moderate, 3=aggressive (default: 1).
.TP
.B \-\-level \fIN\fR
Test level: 1=basic, 2=extended, 3=comprehensive (default: 1).
.SS Performance
.TP
.B \-\-rate \fIN\fR
Maximum HTTP requests per second (default: 5). This is a global politeness
limit; lower it for fragile targets, raise it for lab benchmarks.
.TP
.B \-\-depth \fIN\fR
Crawl depth limit (default: 2).
.TP
.BR \-\-time\-samples ", " \-\-time\-delay
Time-based SQLi sampling count (default: 6) and delay in seconds (default: 2).
.TP
.B \-\-threads \fIN\fR
Threads for data extraction (default: 1).
.SS Output
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fIFILE\fR
Write the report to a file.
.TP
.B \-\-format \fIFORMAT\fR
Report format: text, json, csv (default: text).
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet " / " \-v ", " \-\-verbose " / " \-\-no\-banner
Minimal output / debug output / suppress the startup banner.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Targeted SQL injection on one parameter:
.B anvil \-t 'http://host/page?id=1' \-p id \-\-sqli
.TP
Full XSS sweep with all modes:
.B anvil \-t 'http://host/search?q=t' \-p q \-\-xss \-\-xss\-all
.TP
SSRF against a URL parameter:
.B anvil \-t 'http://host/fetch?url=x' \-p url \-\-ssrf
.TP
OS command injection:
.B anvil \-t 'http://host/ping?host=x' \-p host \-\-cmdi
.TP
Path traversal / LFI:
.B anvil \-t 'http://host/view?file=a' \-p file \-\-path\-traversal
.TP
Crawl the whole app and write a JSON report:
.B anvil \-t http://host \-\-all \-\-crawl \-o report.json \-\-format json
.SH OUTPUT
Findings are printed to standard output and, with
.BR \-o ,
written to a file in the format selected by
.BR \-\-format .
The
.B json
and
.B csv
formats are stable and intended for CI pipelines and downstream tooling.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Completed successfully (regardless of whether findings were reported).
.TP
.B non-zero
A fatal error occurred (invalid arguments, target unreachable, or an
out-of-scope request was blocked).
.SH RULES OF ENGAGEMENT
ANVIL is for authorized security testing only. Only scan systems you own or
have explicit written permission to test. Enumeration and dump options
(\fB\-\-dump\fR, \fB\-\-dump\-all\fR) retrieve real data and must never be run
against production systems without authorization. The default
.B \-\-rate 5
and
.B \-\-risk 1
settings are conservative; raising them increases load on the target.
.SH AUTHOR
Siddhant Bhattarai.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project documentation and source: https://github.com/siddhantbhattarai/anvil
.PP
